						               													<description>What Fistful of Lead Core Rules are to skirmish level wargaming, Bigger Battles is for large scale wargaming.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The beloved Fistful of Lead card mechanics are still there to drive the action, but now each card controls a unit, rather than one soldier.  &amp;#10;How many units, you ask?  How many cards are in a deck, my friend?  Yep.  You can play 52 units on a table!  That is a bigger battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In most games, each player can control up to 5-6 units and their Commanders and Heroes without much trouble.  &amp;#10;Games can have up to 8 players without slowing down the game.&amp;#10; Now, you can dig out all your old miniatures gathering dust and have a game ready to go in a few minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Experienced wargamers and new players alike will enjoy this game.  &amp;#10;Bigger Battles is perfect for convention games and just one-on-one contests.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
